  "texts": [
    "In step (1), the Test Case Generator takes the ST-code to test (e.g., a function block), a test program template with a task configuration, as well as additional required function blocks for the code to test (e.g., utility functions) as input.",
    "The code to test is appended to a prompt for test case generation (detailed later) and sent to an LLM (step 2).",
    "The LLM generates the desired test cases as a CSV file containing test states, input values, and expected output values.",
    "Using a CSV file instead of directly prompting for STcode avoids any LLM-caused syntax errors and saves output tokens.",
    "The LLM then sends the CSV file back to the Test Case Generator (step 3), which converts it into executable STcode."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}